Maris Stella School in Berea congratulated its top learners for outstanding achievements in the 2019 Independent Examination Board (IEB) matric exams. Amy Randelhoff also the Dux recipient for 2019 obtained nine Distinctions and was in the top one percent in the country for four of her subjects. Lucy Paynter was placed in the top one percent in the country for two subjects, obtaining six distinctions. Julia Blythe was in the top one percent for business studies also obtaining six distinctions. The other top learners with six distinctions were Rebecca Standage and Chloe Garrioch. “Well done girls for making Maris Stella proud,” said Cindy Hudson, marketing and PR coordinator at the school.